replies.body:
No, I think it's because AP champions are usually focused on burst and gated on cooldowns.

An ad champion with a mix of damage and defense can just keep outputting dps until they die. 1s survivability is 1s more dps.

An ap champion with a mixture of damage and defense just does less damage with their rotation. They get no benefit from 1s more survival, they need enough to last until their cooldowns come up again - it's usually just worth more to build more damage and kill someone with the first rotation.

Besides, you skipped a few.

